---
title: Sweet Corn & Green Pepper Chowder with Old Bay Toast
description: We couldn’t be prouda of this chowda! This creamy soup has all the veggies worth boasting about, like corn, green pepper, and tender potatoes. Cream cheese and melty cheddar are swirled in for extra richness, then, it’s all dolloped with sour cream and garnished with scallions. On the side, there’s toasted baguette slathered with an Old Bay compound butter so you can sop up every last drop.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/61670b8d6a86e654e3012525-0ac49f00.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/sweet-corn-green-pepper-chowder-61670b8d6a86e654e3012525-b47e1c06.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
course: main course
cuisine: North America
time required: 40 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-corn-green-pepper-chowder-61670b8d6a86e654e3012525
nutrition:
  calories: 850 kcal
  fat: 42 g
  saturated fat: 25 g
  carbohydrates: 100 g
  sugar: 20 g
  protein: 16 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1810 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Place @butter{2%tbsp} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; set aside to soften (you'll use it in step 4). Wash and dry produce.

Core, deseed, and dice @long green pepper{1} into ¼-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%oz} into ½-inch pieces. Drain and rinse @corn{13.4%oz}.

Melt butter in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and scallion whites; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @flour{1%tbsp}; cook, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{1%minute}.

Slowly stir @milk{6.75%oz} into pot a splash at a time until fully incorporated. Stir in @water{1 1/2%cups}.

Add potatoes, @veggie stock concentrate{2}, and half the @Old Bay seasoning{1/2} (you'll use more in the next step). Bring to a boil and cook, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are very tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> To test, pierce one potato piece with a fork—it should go through easily.

Meanwhile, combine softened butter, @Old Bay seasoning{1/4%tsp}, and @sugar{1/4%tsp} until smooth.

> If the butter is still cold, microwave for ~{10%seconds} to soften. Taste and add more Old Bay Seasoning if desired.

Halve @demi-baguette{1} lengthwise; spread cut sides with Old Bay butter. Place cut sides up on a #baking sheet{}.

Toast on top rack until golden, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Once potatoes are tender, reduce heat to low and mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} to desired consistency.

> We recommend mashing until almost smooth, leaving a few small potato pieces for texture.

Stir in @cream cheese{2%tbsp}, corn, and @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}(grated) until fully incorporated and chowder is thick and creamy (it will be very thick at this point). If needed, stir in splashes of water until chowder reaches desired consistency. Season generously with salt and pepper.

Halve Old Bay toast on a diagonal if desired.

Divide chowder between #bowls{}. Garnish with scallion greens and @sour cream{2%tbsp}. Serve with Old Bay toast on the side.